title: Shinsuke Nakamura receives response by AJ Styles for WrestleMania 33 match challenge | GiveMeSport
text:
Shinsuke Nakamura receives response by AJ Styles for WrestleMania 33 match challenge Published 24/7 
WrestleMania 33 is fast approaching but there are several big-name WWE superstars that don't have a match for the show, and they don't have much speculation surrounding them as to who they could be facing either. 
One of these superstars is AJ Styles. His WrestleMania plans could change if he manages to win in the Battle Royal on SmackDown Live this week. However, if he doesn't, he still won't have an opponent for The Showcase of The Immortals. 
Speaking to Yahoo! Sports Japan , Shinsuke Nakamura has announced that he would like to face The Phenomenal One at WrestleMania 33 later this year if the opportunity presents itself. SIGN UP NOW 
Want to become a GMS writer? Sign up now and submit a 250-word test article: http://gms.to/haveyoursay4 Article continues below 
The King of Strong Style said, according to a transcription by Chris Charlton on Twitter: "If the [WrestleMania] opportunity presented itself, I want to do it. AJ doesn't have an opponent yet, I'd like to fill that spot. I've achieved a lot this year, but there's much more to do. I want to make more strides over the next year and show my true ability." 
Nakamura vs Styles is a match that many members of WWE universe would love to see, as fans have fallen in love with both superstars since they made their debuts in NXT and on the main roster respectively last year. Having this clash at WrestleMania would just be the icing on the cake. Article continues below
